# Privacy Policy for Hishab Potro

**Effective Date:** [19th jan 2026]

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Hishab Potro ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our mobile application.

By using the Hishab Potro app, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

## 1. Information We Collect

We collect the following types of information to provide and improve our service to you:

*   **Information You Provide Directly:**
    *   **Customer Information:** When you add a customer, we collect and store the customer's name and, optionally, their phone number. This information is stored locally on your device.
    *   **Transaction Information:** We collect and store all financial transaction details that you manually enter into the app, including amounts, descriptions, dates, and due dates. This data is also stored locally on your device.
    *   **Shop Name:** We store the name of your shop or business, which you provide in the app's settings.

*   **Information Collected with Your Permission:**
    *   **Contact Information:** With your explicit permission, we access your device's contacts to make it easier for you to add new customers. We only use the selected contact's name and phone number for the purpose of pre-filling the "add customer" form. We do not store your entire contact list.
    *   **Profile Picture:** With your permission, you can select an image from your device's gallery to use as your profile picture within the app. This image is stored locally.

*   **Information Collected Automatically:**
    *   **Google Account Information:** When you choose to sign in with your Google account, we receive your name and email address from Google for the purpose of identifying you within the app.
    *   **Usage Data (via Firebase Analytics):** We use Firebase Analytics to collect information about how you use the app, such as the features you use and the time you spend in the app. This helps us understand how to improve the user experience. This data is anonymized and does not personally identify you.
    *   **Advertising Data (via Google AdMob):** Our app uses Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use data to provide personalized advertising. This can include your device's advertising ID. You can learn more about how Google handles data in its advertising policies: [https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads](https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads)

## 2. How We Use Your Information

The information we collect is used for the following purposes:

*   **To Provide and Maintain the Service:** To manage your customer records, track transactions, and display financial summaries.
*   **To Personalize Your Experience:** To display your chosen profile picture and shop name.
*   **To Enable Backup and Restore:** To securely back up your data to your personal Google Drive account and to restore it when you need to.
*   **To Improve Our App:** To analyze usage patterns and identify areas for improvement.
*   **To Communicate with You:** To send you notifications about due dates and backup reminders.
*   **To Support Our Business:** To display advertisements, which helps us keep the app free.

## 3. Data Storage and Security

*   **Local Storage:** All your financial data, customer information, and profile picture are stored locally on your device in an SQLite database.
*   **Cloud Backup:** When you use the Google Drive backup feature, an encrypted copy of your app's database is uploaded to a private folder within your own Google Drive account. We do not have access to this folder or the data stored within it. The data is encrypted using a key that is stored securely on your device.

We are committed to protecting your data. We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

## 4. Third-Party Services

We use the following third-party services to operate our app. These services have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to review them.

*   **Google Sign-In & Google Drive API:** We use these services for user authentication and for creating encrypted backups in your personal Google Drive. By using these features, you are also subject to the [Google Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy).
*   **Google AdMob:** Our app includes the Google Mobile Ads SDK to show advertisements. You can learn more about how Google handles data in its [advertising policies](https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads).
*   **Firebase (Analytics and Remote Config):** We use Firebase for usage analytics and to remotely configure certain features of the app. You can learn more about Firebase's privacy practices here: [https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy](https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy)

## 5. Data Deletion

You have the right to delete your data.

*   **Local Data:** Uninstalling the Hishab Potro application will delete all data stored locally on your device.
*   **Cloud Backup Data:** To delete the backup file stored on Google Drive, you must go to your Google Drive account, find the data for "Hishab Potro", and manually delete it.

## 6. Children's Privacy

Our service does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under age 13 without verification of parental consent, we will take steps to remove that information from our servers.

## 7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy in the app and updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this Privacy Policy. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

